		<descript>
			<abstract>New York City Historical Building Footprints, 2026 is a polygon theme representing the perimeter extent of buildings that have been demolished or significantly altered in New York City since 2004.  Additional attribute information maintained for each feature includes: Building Identification Number (BIN); Borough, Block, and Lot information; ground elevation at building base; roof height above ground elevation; construction year; demolition year; and feature type. Columbia Libraries staff downloaded this dataset from the NYCMap Hub at https://nycmaps-nyc.hub.arcgis.com/datasets/nyc::building-historic/about reprojected it to state plane coordinates and reformatted to the geopackage format in March of 2026.  Additional information about the data may be found at https://github.com/CityOfNewYork/nyc-geo-metadata/blob/main/Metadata/Metadata_BuildingHistoric.md</abstract>
			<purpose>Use of the data is for analytic and cartographic purposes.</purpose>
			<langdata>en</langdata>
		</descript>
